RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH: Doutora em Neurobiologia/Neurocincias pelo Leibniz Institute for Neurobiology, Magdeburg Alemanha. Estudou os mecanismos moleculares responsveis pela plasticidade enceflica e pela plasticidade sinptica homeosttica. Mestre em Bioqumica pela Universidade Federal de Santa Maria (UFSM), com especializao em memria e comportamento. Graduada em Farmcia pela UFSM. Professora adjunta do Departamento de Bioqumica da Universidade Federal de Pernambuco (UFPE) e pesquisadora do Ncleo de Pesquisa em Inovao Teraputica Suely Galdino NUPIT http://dgp.cnpq.br/dgp/espelhogrupo/9706295167857103. Pesquisadora do Programa de Ps-Graduao em Inovao Teraputica (PPGIT).Atualmente, professora visitante na Universidade de Stanford, no laboratrio da Dra. Michelle Monje, lder mundial em pesquisas na rea de neuro-oncologia. Realizou ps-doutorado (2023) no Department of Neurobiology and Anatomy da McGovern Medical School, The University of Texas Health Science Center. A Dra. Melgarejo desenvolve pesquisas nas reas de: (1) neuromodulao de distrbios psicolgicos e cognitivos; (2) novas alternativas teraputicas de origem natural e por sntese qumica para distrbios psicolgicos, neurolgicos e neuro-oncolgicos; e (3) interao entre o sistema nervoso central e a tumorignese.
RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH-EN: Ph.D. in Neurobiology/Neuroscience from the Leibniz Institute for Neurobiology, Magdeburg Germany. Studied the molecular mechanisms responsible for brain plasticity and homeostatic synaptic plasticity. Holds a Masters degree in Biochemistry from the Federal University of Santa Maria (UFSM), with a specialization in memory and behavior. Bachelor's degree in Pharmacy from UFSM. Currently an Associate Professor in the Department of Biochemistry at the Federal University of Pernambuco (UFPE) and a researcher at the Suely Galdino Therapeutic Innovation Research Center NUPIT http://dgp.cnpq.br/dgp/espelhogrupo/9706295167857103. Researcher in the Graduate Program in Therapeutic Innovation (PPGIT).Currently a visiting professor at Stanford University in the laboratory of Dr. Michelle Monje, a global leader in neuro-oncology research. Postdoctoral fellowship (2023) completed at the Department of Neurobiology and Anatomy, McGovern Medical School, The University of Texas Health Science Center. Dr. Melgarejo's research focuses on (1) neuromodulation of psychological and cognitive disorders; (2) novel therapeutic alternatives derived from natural products and chemical synthesis for psychological, neurological, and neuro-oncological disorders; and (3) the interaction between the central nervous system and tumorigenesis.
